respStmt.name: Dropsie College for Hebrew and Cognate Learning

supportDesc.extent: 299 leaves : 230 x 160 (180 x 100) mm bound to 240 x 180 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Paper, 298 leaves; [596-1], modern pagination in reverse order. Mostly gatherings of 20 leaves, with some 18 or 22; at least 3 leaves missing.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in maghribī script in dark brown ink; pointed and vocalized.

binding.p: 19th- or 20th-century quarter leather with spine title Koran.

origin.p: Copy completed by Ibrāhīm ibn Aḥmad ibn ʻImād? al-Ḥanāshī (p. [598]), possibly in the 17th or 18th century.

history.provenance: Formerly in the collection of the Orientalisches Institut (founded in 1886), Universität Wien (label, front cover).
Formerly owned by the Dropsie College for Hebrew and Cognate Learning (note on label, front cover).
